article.headline: Miami (Ohio) 74, Indiana St. 58
article.story: OXFORD, Ohio (AP) -- Michael Bramos scored 17 points to lead Miami of Ohio to a 74-58 win over Indiana State on Tuesday night. The RedHawks (4-3) trailed by 10 points almost six minutes into the first half, but quickly closed the gap and never looked back. Eric Pollitz made a 3-pointer for Miami to tie it at 17 with 10:35 left in the half and the RedHawks led the rest of the game. Tyler Dierkers scored 14 points, Carl Richburg had 13 and Tim Pollitz added 12. The RedHawks shot 55 percent from the floor, including 44 percent (7 of 16) 3-pointers. Gabriel Moore led Indiana State (3-4) with 17 points. Indiana State shot 46 percent from the field, but made only 5 of 21 3-point attempts.
